Position: HIS Business Intelligence Data Analyst
Program: Health Information Systems
Department: Health Services
Reports To: HIS Business Intelligence Manager
Compensation: $38.46 per hour
Status: 100%, Full-Time, Non-Exempt, Confidential
Probation: 90 days
Benefits: Medical, Vision, Dental, and Life Insurance; also including Long-Term Disability, an Employee Assistance Program, and a 403(b)-retirement plan

JOB SUMMARY: The Health Information Systems (HIS) Unit provides software and hardware support to the Health Services (HS) Department of the Los Angeles LGBT Center (Center). HIS administrates and supports all health information systems including the Electronic Health Record (EHR), Pharmacy Management Software, and all supporting/ancillary software applications to support the mission of HS. This position will provide Business Intelligence support to the financial and clinical operations of the Center and is responsible for collecting, scrubbing, and extracting data from various sources to generate reports, dashboards, and analytical solutions. The position will routinely perform and manage standard and advance reporting/analytics and derive insights to drive business decisions and operations. The position will be responsible to manage and maintain accurate, complete, and timely routine reports/analysis and to prepare ad-hoc reports/analysis in understanding and support of business initiatives. The Business Intelligence Analyst will also assist in the design and development of healthcare data feeds, interfaces, SQL Server Data Warehouses and other related needs.

ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:
1) Support the buildout of the Analytics and Reporting platform;
2) Create clear reporting on requested business metrics using Tableau and other reporting tools;
3) Design, develop and maintain custom reports using SQL programming, SQL Server Reporting Services (SSRS);
4) Use data visualization, data manipulation, and pattern recognition to support problem resolution;
5) Extract, analyze, and interpret healthcare and/or financial data to address business needs;
6) Perform analysis on healthcare data using problem-solving and analytical skills, correlating with business processes and assisting management by developing solutions to business issues;
7) Collaborate with leadership to provide meaningful and credible feedback on reporting capabilities and needs;
8) Collaborate with management and other business process owners to gather report requirements and specifications to design, develop and deliver reporting solutions which meet business and IT objectives;
9) Conduct routine data validation and identify ways to improve data reliability, efficiency, and quality;
10) Participate in development and deployment of Tableau reports;
11) Participate in formal training classes, conferences and self-instruction as needed;
12) Properly log and enter work orders into the work order system;
13) Create supporting documentation that can be referenced by business stakeholders;
14) Assist with completion of special projects as requested by various internal departments, or in support of requests from regulatory agencies, contracting agencies, or other external organizations;
15) Collaborate with internal technology teams for urgent and complex issues;
16) Be knowledgeable about and apply company policies to customer requests;
17) Other duties as assigned;

JOB QUALIFICATIONS AND EXPERIENCE:
1) Knowledge of or experience working with the LGBTQ community and familiarity with issues of particular relevance to LGBTQ people;
2) A passion for the Center’s work and its mission to make the world a better place for LGBTQ people;
3) Undergraduate in engineering, Data Analysis, Mathematics, Statistics or Computer Science (master’s preferred);
4) 5-7 years industry experience in IT relational databases and SQL reporting;
5) 5-7 years of increasingly complex experience in quantifying, measuring, and analyzing financial/performance management metrics;
6) Healthcare provider operational workflow knowledge and experience highly preferred;
7) Experience working with EHR and Practice Management systems preferred;
8) Experience with clinical workflows;
9) Expert level with Microsoft Business Intelligence tools and Tableau;
10) Knowledge of data warehousing and business intelligence platforms;
11) Knowledge of data visualization and reporting techniques;
12) Highly analytical with ability to translate complex information into simpler terms and concepts;
13) Experience creating SQL queries from scratch (including complex stored procedures) and data processes;
14) Expert with data reporting tools Tableau, SSRS, Excel and Access;
15) Expert MSBI developer (SSIS, SSRS and SSAS);
16) Excellent SQL scripting skills;
17) Familiar with relational data modelling, 3NF, database integrity;
18) Demonstrated business acumen with the ability to quickly learn what we do and why we do it;
19) Ability to maintain confidentiality;
20) Ability to pay attention to little things and ensure tasks and assignments are completed in timely and appropriate manner;
21) A clear and effective communicator, both written and verbal, both internally and externally;
22) Demonstrated ability to work effectively with people of diverse races, ethnicities, nationalities, sexual orientations, gender identities, gender expression, socio-economic backgrounds, religions, ages, English-speaking abilities, immigration status, and physical abilities in a multicultural environment.

